title: $:/plugins/rimir/dashboard/settings

! Dashboard settings

!! Marking a dashboard

Tag a tiddler with <<tag "$:/tags/rimir/dashboard">>. A view-template body cascade entry (`$:/config/ViewTemplateBodyFilters/rimir-dashboard`, ordered before `default`) swaps its body to the dashboard canvas.

!! Tile tiddlers

Tiles are tiddlers tagged <<tag "$:/tags/rimir/dashboard/tile">> with these fields:

|!Field |!Meaning |
|`dashboard` |Title of the dashboard this tile belongs to |
|`target` |Title of the tiddler shown inside the tile |
|`x` / `y` |Top-left position in pixels, relative to the canvas |
|`w` / `h` |Width / height in pixels |

Geometry is written by a small `<$dashboard-drag>` widget on pointer release via a plain `$action-setfield` — the values are ordinary editable fields.

!! Tile actions menu

Each tile's actions live behind a ⋮ menu in the corner (revealed on hover), opened on hover or keyboard focus: ↗ open-external (when available), ⧉ show-in-popup, ⊟ toggle window/bare, × remove.

!! What a tile shows

By default a tile transcludes its `target`'s body; if the target has no (or empty) `text` but has an `icon`, the tile shows the icon instead. You can override what a tile shows, in three layers (first that applies wins):

# ''Per tile'' — the tile's `display` field names a field of the target (or `body`). Set it from the tile's ⋮ menu (//Show//: auto / body / icon, or type any field name).
# ''Per dashboard'' — //display rules//: tiddlers tagged <<tag "$:/tags/rimir/dashboard/display-rule">> with a `dashboard` (the dash id), a `filter` (matched against a tile's `target`) and a `field`. The first rule, in `order`, whose filter selects the target sets the field. Edit them from the //Display rules// panel on the dashboard.
# ''Default'' — `text` → body, else `icon` → icon.

When the resolved field's value names an existing tiddler (e.g. `icon` pointing at an image/SVG tiddler) it is transcluded; otherwise the field's own value is rendered as wikitext (so an inline-SVG `icon` works too).

!! Opening a link in a new browser tab

If a tile's `target` tiddler has one of the //external-open fields// below, the tile shows an ↗ action and ''Ctrl/Cmd-clicking'' the tile opens that value in a new browser tab (like Ctrl-clicking a link). Plain click still opens the target in the wiki.

The fields are tried in order; the first non-empty one wins. Edit the space-separated list to add your own (e.g. `href`, `link`) or change the priority:

<$edit-text tiddler="$:/config/rimir/dashboard/external-open-fields" tag="input" default="url _canonical_uri" class="tc-edit-texteditor" placeholder="url _canonical_uri"/>

Absolute URLs (`https://…`, `//host/…`, `/path`) open as-is; a bare host gets `https://` prepended. This is how an uploaded image or file tile (which carries `_canonical_uri`) opens its raw file in a new tab.
